observationText: The CFPAC-1 cell line was derived from a liver metastasis of a 26-year-old male patient with cystic fibrosis who had a well-differentiated adenocarcinoma in the head of the pancreas and multiple liver metastases.
The CFPAC-1 cell line was derived from a pancreatic epithelial adenocarcinoma.
The CFPAC-1 cell line is a null control for the cystic fibrosis transmembrane conductance regulator (CFTR) gene.
The CFPAC-1 cell line exhibits a range of 300-800 passages.
